all_features = all_features[, !grepl('RMSE', names(all_features))] # remove pseudo features
meta_df = data.frame(filename = all_features$filename)
meta_df = add_meta_data(meta_df)
all_features = all_features[!grepl('name', names(all_features))] # remove columns containing the word 'name'
# remove meta data, BUT keep emotion
all_features = all_features[!names(all_features) %in% c("speaker", "sentence_ID", "sentence")]
interesting_cols = names(all_features)[names(all_features) != "emotion"]

print(paste(length(interesting_cols), "features remain:", paste(interesting_cols, collapse = ", ")))
## [1] "63 features remain: w0_PC1, w0_PC2, w1_PC1, w1_PC2, w2_PC1, w2_PC2, w3_PC1, w3_PC2, reference_angle_w0_PC1, reference_angle_w0_PC2, reference_angle_w1_PC1, reference_angle_w1_PC2, reference_angle_w2_PC1, reference_angle_w2_PC2, reference_angle_w3_PC1, reference_angle_w3_PC2, angle_to_angle_w0_PC1, angle_to_angle_w0_PC2, angle_to_angle_w1_PC1, angle_to_angle_w1_PC2, angle_to_angle_w2_PC1, angle_to_angle_w2_PC2, angle_to_angle_w3_PC1, angle_to_angle_w3_PC2, compression_rate, peak_frequency, peak_amplitude, st_compression_rate, st_peak_frequency, st_peak_amplitude, smallest_harmonic, max_freq, relative_harmonic, stylized_INTSINT_count, MOMEL_INTSINT_count, num_accents, Aa_mean, Aa_1, Aa_last, a, b, naive_intercept, naive_slope, min_max_slope, num_phrases, Ap, phrase_T0, phrase_reg_slope, phrase_naive_slope, num_ICCs, num_pos_ICCs, num_neg_ICCs, mean_delta_F0, sd_delta_F0, mean_tc, sd_tc, mean_delta_tc, sd_delta_tc, EAC, skewness, kurtosis, entropy, sd"
first = TRUE
for (col in interesting_cols){
  str_formula = as.formula(paste(col, "~ emotion"))
  wc_test = data.frame(ggpubr::compare_means(str_formula, data = all_features))
  if (first){
    count_df = data.frame(group1 = wc_test$group1, group2 = wc_test$group2,  count  = as.numeric(wc_test$p.signif != "ns"))
    first = FALSE
  } else {
    if (all(wc_test$group1 == count_df$group1) & all(wc_test$group2 == count_df$group2)){
      count_df$count = count_df$count + as.numeric(wc_test$p.signif != "ns")
    }
  }
}
plot_significant_emotion_heatmap = function(data_set_name){
  # Plot heat map of emotion X emotion number of significantly different
  #min_count = min(count_df$count)
  min_count = 40
  library(ggplot2)
  ggplot(count_df, aes(y=group1, x=group2, fill=count)) + geom_tile(colour="white", width=.9, height=.9) +
    theme_minimal() +  scale_fill_gradientn(
      colours=colorRampPalette(c("#e7f0fa", "#c9e2f6", "#95cbee", "#0099dc", "#4ab04a", "#ffd73e"))(10),
      limits=c(min_count, length(interesting_cols)),
      breaks=seq(min_count, length(interesting_cols), length=6),
      na.value=rgb(246, 246, 246, max=255),
      labels=floor(seq(min_count, length(interesting_cols), length=6)),
      guide=guide_colourbar(ticks=T, nbin=50, barheight=.5, label=T, barwidth=10)
    ) +
    theme(
      legend.position=c(.5, -.25),
      legend.direction="horizontal",
      legend.text=element_text(colour="grey20"),
      plot.margin=grid::unit(c(.5,.5,2,.5), "cm"),
      panel.grid=element_blank(),
      axis.text.y=element_text(size=10, family="Helvetica"),
      axis.text.x=element_text(size=10),
      title=element_text(family="Helvetica"),
    ) +
    ggtitle(paste("Significant Wilcoxon tests between emotions for", data_set_name)) +
    xlab("Emotions") +
    ylab("Emotions")
  
  # if (!is.null(save_as)){
  #   ggsave(save_as)
  # }
}

#plot_significant_emotion_heatmap("new dynamic features", save_as="new_features.pdf")
print(plot_significant_emotion_heatmap("new dynamic features"))

create_correlation_heatmap = function(df, NA_cols = c(), title = NULL){
  NA_cols = c(NA_cols, "filename") # also remove filename for the correlation matrix
  df = df[, !names(df) %in% NA_cols]
  print(paste(nrow(df) - nrow(na.omit(df)), "rows were removed"))
  corr_df = cor(na.omit(df))
  library(rstatix)
  corr_df = corr_df %>% cor_gather()
  corr_df$cor = abs(corr_df$cor)
  
  p = ggplot(corr_df, aes(y=var1, x=var2, fill=cor)) + 
    labs(x = "features", y = "features", fill = "Absolute correlation") +
    geom_tile(colour="white") + 
    theme_minimal() +  
    # scale_fill_gradientn(
    #   colours=heat.colors(10),
    #   #colours=colorRamp(c("#ffffff", "#000000"))(10),
    #   limits=c(-1, 1),
    #   breaks=seq(-1, 1, length=3),
    #   na.value=rgb(246, 246, 246, max=255),
    #   labels=floor(seq(-1, 1, length=3)),
    #   guide=guide_colourbar(ticks=T, nbin=50, barheight=.5, label=T, barwidth=10)
    # ) +
    
  theme(
      axis.text.x=element_blank(),
      axis.ticks.x=element_blank(),
      axis.text.y=element_blank(),
      axis.ticks.y=element_blank()
    ) + 
    scale_fill_gradient(low = "white", high = "black")
  
  if (!is.null(title)){
    p = p + ggtitle(title)
  }
  
  print(p)
}
all_features = all_features[!names(all_features) == "emotion"]
eGeMAPS = eGeMAPS[, 1:88]
create_correlation_heatmap(eGeMAPS, title = "eGeMAPs")
